<HEADLINE>
FT  07 FEB 94 / UK Company News: M&amp;G plan approved
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shareholders in M&amp;G Group, the unit trust company, have overwhelmingly
approved a controversial executive share option scheme which allows exercise
without any reference to performance criteria.
The scheme had been opposed by the National Association of Pension Funds,
one of the UK's largest shareholder groups, which has urged companies to set
performance criteria for the exercise of options that tied rewards for
executives more closely to rewards for shareholders.
