<HEADLINE>
FT  07 FEB 94 / EU monetary body enjoys Bank approval
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER NORMAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The European Monetary Institute, which started operating last month, should
be able to help European Union central banks control inflation, the Bank of
England believes, Peter Norman writes.
In an article released ahead of tomorrow's Quarterly Bulletin the Bank says
that the institute 'should be able to contribute to robust
counter-inflationary monetary policies' by monitoring policies and
recommending changes.
The article, timed to appear before tomorrow's meeting of the institute's
decision-making council, makes clear that the Bank wants the institute to
play a constructive role in Europe's economic future.
