<TEXT>
Mr Alejandro Noemi has resigned as president of Codelco, Chile's state
copper company, shortly after the publication of an internal report
confirming losses of some Dollars 206m on metals futures trading.
Mr Noemi, who led the internal probe, said: 'I am pained by this huge stain
on my record and I have only continued (as president) in order to complete
the investigation and control the damage.'
Codelco's report concluded that failure to implement controls had allowed Mr
Juan Pablo Davila, the chief futures trader, to mount more than 5,000
operations last year leading to losses of Dollars 206.7m.
