Department, Financial Times, Number One Southwark Bridge, London SE1 9HL, by
Friday March 4,1994.
2. The closing date for receipt of entries is Friday March 4,1994. Proof of
posting is not proof of receipt. No responsibility is accepted for entries
lost, damaged or delayed in the post.
3. This competition is open to all readers over the age of 18, other than
employees or their immediate family of the Promoter, or any agency or any
other person directly associated with this competition. Only the closest
entry per household will be considered.
4. By entering this competition, the Entrant will be deemed to have read and
understood those rules of which the entry instructions form part and to be
bound by them.
5. Prizes will be awarded in order of merit to those entrants who correctly
answer questions 1-3 and who in the judges' opinion have most closely
estimated the number of miles Arnie (or Lucy as his stand-in if Arnie is
incapacitated) will have skied by the end of February. In the event of a
tie, or ties, winning entrants will be invited to enter a separate play-off
competition.
6. There is no cash alternative to the prizes. The decisions of the panel of
judges shall be final and binding and no correspondence will be entered
into.
7. Prize winners will be notified within 28 days of the date of judging.
