FT  05 FEB 94 / International Company News: Paramount prefers Viacom
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The board of Paramount, the US communications group at the centre of a
Dollars 10bn takeover battle, yesterday urged shareholders to accept a bid
from cable TV company Viacom and to bring a speedy end to the five-month
battle.
Paramount warned that the long-drawn out bid risked damaging its business,
and asked shareholders to accept Viacom's offer by the bidding deadline of
February 14.
If neither Viacom nor rival bidder QVC gets a majority of the company's
shares by the deadline, Paramount said it would bring the bidding procedure
to a close. That could leave both bidders still struggling for control of
the group.
There is little to choose between the Viacom and QVC offers on price, though
Viacom's bid includes a slightly higher cash element and guarantees for
Paramount shareholders if Viacom shares fall in value over the next year.
</TEXT>
