<HEADLINE>
FT  05 FEB 94 / International Company News: Telmex profits disappoint
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LUHNOW
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Telefonos de Mexico, Mexico's largest private company, lifted net profits by
4.5 per cent in real terms last year, to 9bn pesos (Dollars 2.9bn), writes
David Luhnow in Mexico City.
But the results of the telephone monopoly failed to meet analysts'
expectations, largely because of a fourth-wuarter 250m-peso write-off on
obsolete equipment.
Analysts estimated the company's earnings were about Dollars 1.40 per
American depositary receipt for the fourth quarter, and Dollars 5.47 a share
for the year, against Dollars 4.84 for 1992.
Net sales were 24.6bn pesos during 1993, up 10 per cent from 22.4bn pesos in
1992. Operating income amounted to 10.28bn pesos for the year, also up 10
per cent.
