FT  05 FEB 94 / UK Company News: ECIC raises Pounds 17.2m in placing
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Energy Capital Investment Company, an investment vehicle specialising in
project finance for the oil and gas industry in the US, yesterday announced
it had raised Pounds 17.2m in an institutional placing.
The company said institutional investors had subscribed for five shares and
one warrant at a unit price of Pounds 5. A total of 18m shares and 3.6m
warrants had been placed, about half of which was taken by UK institutions.
The shares are expected to begin trading on February 10.
