<HEADLINE>
FT  05 FEB 94 / Gatt praises Australia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCES WILLIAMS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   GENEVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Australia's programme of economic and trade reform yesterday wonpraise from
trading partners as a model for others to follow, Frances Williams reports
from Geneva.
A Gatt secretariat report on the country's trade policies and practices,
says Australia has pressed ahead with far-reaching reforms despite recession
and big balance of payments deficits. However, Gatt chides Australia for
high tariffs on items such as cars (up to 30 per cent) and clothing (up to
47 per cent).
